<p>I have a SpatialLineDataFrame with 5 columns 'a','b','c','d','e'. The second column is full of zeros and I want to change them. More specifically I want the values of  'b' column to be 2 times bigger than values of column 'a',  if values of 'a' columns are less than 5 and the rest of them to be 10. I tried:</p>  <pre><code>if ((SpatialLineDataFrame@Data$'a') &lt; 5){   SpatialLineDataFrame@Data$'b'= SpatialLineDataFrame@Data$'a' *2 }else{    SpatialLineDataFrame@Data$'b'==10  } </code></pre>  <p>But all I get is the values of column 'a' *2. There are no 10 values where column 'a' is &lt;5. How can I fix this?</p>